A Facebook page titled "The Second Egyptian Revolution of Rage" reads: "Seeing that the situation, under the leadership of the Supreme Council of the Armed Forces, is only going from bad to worse, and since the council has proven from day one that public pressure is the most effective policy for achieving the demands of the legitimate revolution, we have decided to take to the streets and squares [once again] and demonstrate throughout Egypt until our demands are met..."<ref name="memri1">{{cite news|title=Disappointed with Revolution's Gains, Egyptians Renew Protests|url=http://www.memri.org/report/en/0/0/0/0/0/0/5429.htm|accessdate=5 July 2011|newspaper=http://www.memri.org/|date=3 July 2011}}</ref> On the 1st July, tens of thousands of protesters gathered in Suez, Alexandria and Tahrir Square in Cairo, to voice frustrations with the ruling Supreme Council of the Armed Forces for what they perceived to be the slow pace of change, five months after Mubarak's ousting<ref>{{cite web|url=http://channel6newsonline.com/2011/07/thousands-of-egyptians-protest-against-police-brutality/ |title=Channel 6 News Â» Thousands of Egyptians protest against police brutality |publisher=Channel6newsonline.com |date= |accessdate=2011-07-02}}</ref> calling it the '''"Friday of Retribution"'''<ref>http://www.thedailynewsegypt.com/egypt/thousands-demonstrate-on-friday-of-retribution.html</ref>.

On 4 July 2011, an explosion at the pipeline near [[Nagah]] in the Sinai Peninsula haltied natural gas supplies to Israel and Jordan.<ref name=aljazeera040711/> An official said that armed men with machine guns forced guards at the station to leave before planting explosive charge there.<ref name=aljazeera040711/> This is the third attack on Egyptian gas pipelines since an uprising overthrew Hosni Mubarak.<ref name=aljazeera040711/> There was also a failed attempt to attack the pipeline in March.<ref name=aljazeera040711>{{cite news | agency = [[Al Jazeera]]| url= http://english.aljazeera.net/news/middleeast/2011/07/2011740176861868.html | title = Blast hits Egyptian gas pipeline | date = 2011-07-04 | accessdate=2011-07-04}}</ref>
